British Airways launched its new dining experience for Nairobi-London at NAS Airport facility, JKIA, on Tuesday. Guests were served and addressed by NAS and British Airways inflight head chef Nairobi Timothy Njoroge. In attendance, too, was NAS airport services MD Eric Rouvillois, BA regional commercial manager, Trade East and Southern Africa Sue Petrie, corporate sales manager South Africa, airport manager Kenya Susan Ombele and BA trade sales manager Kenya Permie Dadhiala. The launch comes after British Airways announced a Sh585 billion investment plan for its customers in a number of African countries, including Kenya.The investment includes 72 new aircraft, expanded routes, flight frequencies, new in-flight dining and improved cabin experience for customers.